<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: WILSON SIGNS WITH SWEDISH BASKETBALL TEAM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Sara Wilson, a former Hart High basketball standout, has signed a contract 
with Bro Basket in Orebro, Sweden. 
</P>
<P>
 Wilson, a four-year starter at the University of Oregon and an All-Pacific 10 
selection, led Hart to Southern Section titles in 1989 and 1990. 
</P>
<P>
 Bro Basket is one of 14 teams in Sweden's Division I professional league and 
finished third in the Swedish playoffs last year. 
</P>
<P>
 Wilson, a 6-foot-3 center, will report to the team Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Gerald Madkins of the Cleveland Cavaliers is the scheduled guest speaker at 
the ProTech basketball camp Aug. 22-26 at Burbank High. 
</P>
<P>
 Daily sessions, open to boys between the ages of 11 and 17, run from 8 a.m. to 
1 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: 818-725-7988. Karate 
</P>
<P>
 Paris Blumenthal won the Amateur Athletic Union USA Karate Championship in 
Villa Park, Ill., last month. Blumenthal, a fifth-degree black belt in Okinawan 
Matsubayai Shorin-Ryu karate, defeated three-time national champion Al Doorlag. 
Softball 
</P>
<P>
 Quartz Hill's bid to reach the Senior Girls Softball World Series fell one 
game short when it suffered consecutive losses to Pinole, Calif. 
</P>
<P>
 Quartz Hill made it to the championship game of the double-elimination 
tournament without a defeat. But Pinole swept a doubleheader from Quartz Hill, 
3-1 and 6-1, to advance to Kalamazoo, Mich. Vicki McKay, a freshman pitcher 
from Paraclete High, threw two no-hitters in tournament games. Motor Sports 
</P>
<P>
 Positions are still available for Friday night's Ventura County Fair 
destruction derby. There is an entry fee of $50 and each member of the crew is 
required to purchase a $15 pit pass. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: 805-656-1122. 
</P>
