MINER KILLED IN KENTUCKY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A cave-in killed a miner Tuesday in southeastern Kentucky, the state's seventh 
coal mine fatality this year, authorities said. Keith Gibson, 22, of Knox 
County was trapped when the roof he was bolting collapsed. 
</P>
