<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: YOUTH ORCHESTRA AUDITIONS PLANNED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TRACY WILSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Young musicians from the Conejo Valley and surrounding communities are 
encouraged to attend auditions for the Conejo Youth Symphony on Aug. 30 and 31. 
</P>
<P>
 The group, which is composed of students ages 21 and younger, is sponsored by 
the Conejo Symphony Orchestra and will perform three concerts in the new Forum 
Theatre at the Civic Arts Plaza during the 1994-95 season.Auditions will be 
held from 4:30 p.m. to 7 p.m. at Cal Lutheran University, Room K-1. Returning 
members do not need to audition. 
</P>
<P>
 Students should bring a short musical piece that they are currently studying 
and will be asked to play a brief portion of sight-reading and scales. 
</P>
<P>
 Tuition for the Conejo Youth Symphony is $90 or $140 for two or more students 
from the same family. 
</P>
<P>
 For audition appointments, call 495-6833. TRACY WILSON 
</P>
</TEXT>
