<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LOS ANGELES; SCHOOL 
BOARD VOTES TO OPPOSE 'SOS' INITIATIVE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Los Angeles Board of Education members voted 6 to 0 this week to oppose 
Proposition 187, the "save our state" immigration initiative on the Nov. 8 
state ballot. 
</P>
<P>
 The measure would require expulsion of illegal immigrants from California's 
public schools and deny them most health care and social services.  
</P>
<P>
 Supporters, including the state Republican party, Gov. Pete Wilson and several 
taxpayer groups, say the measure is needed to cut costs and stem illegal 
immigration. 
</P>
<P>
 Opponents, including the California School Boards Assn., the California 
Teachers Assn. and the state Parent Teacher Assn., said the initiative would 
turn educators into immigration enforcers and burden them with additional 
paperwork, cost the state considerable federal funding and hurt children. 
</P>
</TEXT>
