<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY NEWSMAKERS: EXECUTIVE APPOINTED AT HYUNDAI MOTOR FINANCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * Mitchell L. Hogins has been appointed vice president of finance for Hyundai 
Motor Finance Co. in Fountain Valley. He was formerly vice president and 
controller of Security Pacific Auto Finance in Westlake Village and, before 
that, comptroller for the First National Bank of Anchorage.  
</P>
<P>
 * Frank Borst, Tim Crabtree and Gary Smith have been named to positions as 
vice president and officers of Odetics Inc., an Anaheim supplier of information 
management products. Borst is director of global business development and 
managing director of Odetics Asia Pacific. Crabtree is general manager of 
Odetics Broadcast, and Gary Smith is corporate controller. 
</P>
<P>
 * Melanie Tate has joined Lincoln Property Co. in Irvine as director of 
training. She was formerly senior sales trainer for McNeil Real Estate 
Management in Houston. Before that, Tate was a property manager and leasing 
consultant with Landsdowne East in Lexington, Ky.  
</P>
<P>
 * Alan J. Whiley has joined the Orange office of BDO Seidman, an accounting, 
tax and consulting firm, as an audit partner. He previously spent 20 years at 
KPMG. 
</P>
<P>
 * Michael Jackson has been appointed Southwest Area vice president for Coors 
Brewing Co. Jackson joins the Irvine office from Kraft General Foods, where he 
was director of sales for 13 Western states in the frozen desserts division.  
</P>
<P>
 * Donald Danks has been appointed chief executive and president of Advantage 
Life Products Inc., an Irvine health care and beauty aid company. Jim 
Stapleton, who had been serving as interim chief executive, has been named 
executive vice president and chief operating officer. Danks held the chief 
executive position until July, 1993, when the company acquired Lasting 
Cosmetics Inc. At that time, Lasting Cosmetics chief executive Michael Ackerman 
assumed the chief executive post, with Danks remaining president. 
</P>
<P>
 * Paul Knopick has been appointed director of public relations for FHP 
International Corp., a Fountain Valley health care services company. He was 
formerly director of media relations for ICN Pharmaceuticals Inc. and before 
that was with Consumers Power Co. in Michigan, an investor-owned utility.  
</P>
<P>
 * Steve Gough has been appointed general sales manager of Cypress-based 
Mitsubishi Motor Sales of America Inc.'s Southeast region. Gough, who has been 
with the company since 1986, had been franchise development manager for the 
region. 
</P>
<P>
 * Dennis Joyce has been appointed to the newly created position of vice 
president, operations, for Kofax Image Products, an Irvine image-processing 
software and hardware company. He has responsibility for the company's 
manufacturing and quality-control departments. Joyce joined Kofax in 1989 as 
director of manufacturing. Before that, he directed the quality-assurance 
operations at FileNet Corp., and managed the quality-control department at 
Pertec Computer Corp. 
</P>
