December.The agreement was approved in separate meetings this week and is 
contingent on the approval of Macy creditors, the court and Federated 
shareholders. However, creditors have already given their support to the plan, 
under which Federated would repay $4.1 billion in Macy debt and Macy would 
become a Federated division. The companies have not yet revealed how they would 
