efficient disposition of property, saves long-term holding costs and results in 
the best net profit for the seller," said Mark Van Ness, CEO of the brokerage. 
</P>
<P>
 With Alabama partner J.P. King Auction Co., SperryVan Ness will hold its first 
auction Nov. 5 at the Sheraton Los Angeles Airport Hotel. About $50 million in 
property is expected to change hands. 
