<TEXT>
<P>
 An article in Friday's editions inaccurately quoted Ann Stone, national 
chairman of Republicans for Choice in Alexandria, Va. Defending Republican 
Senate candidate Mike Huffington's stand on abortion, Stone said the Santa 
Barbara congressman "is pro-choice not anti-choice. The worst liberal Democrat 
pro-choicers can say is that he is mixed choice." 
</P>
